Answer:
Okay actually im gonna go off on a little rant before i head for my walk.

And now those girls, have found the love of their lives and in an adorable relationship or even married  to the guy that fell in love with them, as a person.
  
  High school for me wasnt easy, it was hard for me to find someone who liked me for me and not so later on they could tell their friends that they dated a "trophy" (yes ive heard it like 100 times) people dont realize the damage that is done when people just want to spread open your legs, instead of get to know you.
  
  When i get in a relationship its constant arguments about the fact so many people hit on me, find me attractive, and the friends i make arent wanting to just be friends - they want more. Ill never be looked at as someone whos loyal cause the people around me flirt with me, its fucked up.
  
  Rape isnt a fun topic but its a serious issue for someone with good features, because despite if they dont want to open their legs, theres sick bastards who believe they should for them.
  
  Yes theres advantages such as: girls respected me growing up or feared me, i got everything handed to me, i got presents that could support an army, teachers treated me like a princess, jobs are super easy to find, and attention is super easy to get
  
  But i need people to understand LIFE ISNT ALL THAT EASY.  So thats what its like lol

Question: how do you feel about marriage?
Answer:
It used to be this religious ceremony or a way for people to have stature in society, but now a days people get married for tax reasons, its just a contract. For a man, marriage isnt that appealing anymore, because 1. Women laws with marriage, they will almost always win. Which is why prenups are so popular now. 2. Divorce has become socially acceptable.
  
  Its really rare for a marriage these days to be successful, theres a lot of negative connotation - psychologically they might turn negative due to the thought "im gonna be with this this person forever" & focus on the aspects of what they dont offer that they see in others.
  
  I told myself that the person i marry will be the person i stay with forever, divorce isnt an option. They are stuck with me whether they like it or not. My parents have been divorced since ive been 3 years old, and it wasnt that bad but ive never known what it was like having two parents in the same house before. Ive always had two rooms, two beds. But at the same time i wouldnt have wanted my parents to stay together- thatd probably be way more miserable. But still I just dont want that for my kids.
